sec.p:
Direct instillation of a concentrated (unstated) solution of aqueous sodium hexametaphosphate into the eyes of New Zealand rabbits induced severe and irreparable ocular damage; identical treatment with 0.2% was said to be “nonirritating” in rabbit eye (reviewed in Lanigan
25
).

Direct eye or skin contact with neat or concentrated (alkaline) phosphates can cause local irritation and severe chemical burns (reviewed in Lanigan
25
).
